sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M30333
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Refactored M13 Between HpaI and BamHI Sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The M13K07 genome was refactored between its unique HpaI and BamHI sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iny Jhun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the M13K07 genome sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Overlaps between various genes were removed and enzymes were inserted between the separated genes, in order to allow for easier manipulation, such as deletion and insertion, of the genes.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M31998
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the part gene 8 of M13K07, which includes a unique enzyme on both ends, and its promoter and RBS.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Iny Jhun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The two enzyme sites on the ends allow easier deletion/insertion.
